  {
    "hotel_id": "800625",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/shilla-stay-seodaemun/hotel/seoul-kr.html",
    "name": "Shilla Stay Seodaemun Seoul Station",
    "detail": "Frequent traveller to Seoul. Staff was very friend and accommodating, as they've just opened about a year ago. One criticism is when I asked about nearby laundry/dry cleaners, as the rates at hotel are expensive and I can speak Korean. They said none were nearby, however there was one about 30m away, around the corner... come on. However, they allowed me to check-in VERY early ahead of the normal check-in time, and service was otherwise top end in my extensive experience staying at hotels in Korea. Room was very small, and odd that if you slide closed the bedroom separating door (never did) there was a window from the bedroom directly into the shower. However, the room/bathroom were all very modern and well kept. No complaints other than size, and as many other business hotels in Seoul there was free WiFi. Not much of a lobby meeting area which meant there was quite often large groups of people hanging around and a bit crowded. Transportation ok - Seodaemun Stn just out front but a bit of a walk my Seoul standards until you hit the train platform. Not bad but not great for grabbing taxis as you need to grab from the corner of the big intersection. Coffee shops nearby, convenience stores nearby, food selection close by is ok, and typical of north of the river areas.",
